description:
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited from Occupational Therapists to join our enthusiastic Integrated Mental Health Team at HMP Liverpool. We are offering a fantastic opportunity to develop knowledge and skills towards your development as a skilled effective practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Secure Division is responsible for specialist secure mental health and learning disability services, for service users with complex needs. You will contribute to the delivery of high standards of care and treatment based at HMP Liverpool, which is a category B prison in the Walton District of Liverpool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will function as an Occupational Therapist to a defined group of service users under the supervision of senior staff working always to the Occupational Therapy Code of Conduct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake the assessment and treatment of service users and manage a case load as required by the needs of the service whilst working as a member of a multi-disciplinary team. Treatment interventions will be up to date and evidence based where possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with your professional qualification, you will need to demonstrate enthusiasm in your attitude, commitment and behaviour towards our service users using effective communication skills and the ability to perform under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisting is planned for 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are planned for 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
